SIMPLE: incoherent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incoherent
<hw>In`co*her"ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>coherent</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>incoh⟦eacute⟧rent</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not coherent; wanting cohesion; loose; unconnected;
physically disconnected; not fixed to each; -- said of material
substances.</def> <rj><au>Woodward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lacking logical coherence or agreement; incongruous;
inconsistent; having no dependence of one part on another; logically
disconnected; rambling; -- of speech or discourse.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The same
rambling, <xex>incoherent</xex> manner.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bp.
Warburton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Exhibiting incoherent{2} speech or thought; -- of
people; <as>as, a confused and <ex>incoherent</ex> accident
victim</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Lacking harmony or congruity of parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incoherentific</ent>⟦br⟧
